ies, the integrated\nHI image shows a ring of roughly constant HI column density surrounding a deep\ncentral depression, whereas in considerably inclined galaxies (i > 45 deg) the\nHI image is characterized by two kidney-shaped density enhancements and a mild\ncentral depression.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 29 Nov 2004 10:51:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
